36:39.468 --> 36:42.001
I don't know, Bart,
that's why I'm calling you.

36:42.926 --> 36:46.000
Well look, do you know of
anybody who might be able to...

36:46.335 --> 36:47.920
- Got a minute?
- Hang on, Bart.

36:48.258 --> 36:49.423
No. What?

36:49.578 --> 36:52.300
I just got a phone call
from Audrey Graves, remember her?

36:52.777 --> 36:56.732
Bart, just see what you can find out
and call me back. Thanks.

36:57.258 --> 36:59.752
So, Audrey, eh?
How's she doing?

36:59.927 --> 37:03.423
Health wise, pretty good. Same with
the baby. She's back to work full time.

37:03.907 --> 37:06.380
- Good.
- She wanted some answers.

37:07.627 --> 37:08.750
About what?

37:09.087 --> 37:10.771
Harlan Sendak.

37:11.277 --> 37:12.680
What about him?

37:12.796 --> 37:14.790
According to Audrey
he was doing some work

37:14.955 --> 37:16.702
- for Lowy Pharmaceuticals.
- Yeah.

37:17.478 --> 37:18.811
Lowy have filed an injunction

37:18.936 --> 37:21.771
that we - NorBAC - are not releasing
research that belongs to them.

37:22.048 --> 37:25.182
NorBAC has nothing to do
with Harlan's personal research.

37:25.497 --> 37:28.142
- Not according to Audrey.
- I don't care.

37:28.797 --> 37:31.432
Harlan Sendak
was a friend of mine.

37:31.838 --> 37:35.622
And he died in a car crash last week.
So what's the problem?

37:36.345 --> 37:39.042
You've been spending a lot of time
on this personal project?

37:39.186 --> 37:40.480
Yeah, so?

37:40.626 --> 37:43.413
So, you should have told me
before using the lab's resources

37:43.605 --> 37:46.602
- and our scientists' time to help you do it.
- Come on, Caroline.

37:47.005 --> 37:48.820
David, we entered
into an agreement

37:49.046 --> 37:51.480
with Audrey Graves
and American Pharmaceuticals.

37:51.698 --> 37:54.150
No, you have entered
into an agreement.

37:54.347 --> 37:57.191
A 35 million dollar agreement, David.

37:57.467 --> 38:00.942
So, if they want to have a look at some
research that they feel is potentially theirs,

38:01.117 --> 38:02.751
we have an obligation
to show it to them.

38:02.926 --> 38:05.051
- It's not theirs.
- Then let them determine that.

38:05.215 --> 38:06.110
No.

38:06.448 --> 38:09.182
Not this stuff.
Not this time. Okay?

38:10.238 --> 38:12.902
Just gimme a break
with this one, Caroline.

38:14.195 --> 38:17.362
- Excuse me.
- Hey. Come on in.

38:21.186 --> 38:23.493
- Anything else?
- Yeah. You work on any outside projects,

38:23.806 --> 38:26.393
you find a cure for the common cold,
you buy a pencil,

38:26.537 --> 38:28.543
I want to know about it.
Understood?

38:28.876 --> 38:30.141
- Sure thing.
- Good.

38:30.375 --> 38:32.063
- Carlos.
- Hey.

38:33.537 --> 38:36.921
- Let's take a walk.
- What was that all about?

38:37.037 --> 38:39.531
Lowy Pharmaceuticals wants
Harlan's research.

38:39.697 --> 38:41.743
- How do you know?
- I met with one of their lawyers.

38:41.886 --> 38:43.131
I was trying to keep things personal,

38:43.266 --> 38:45.550
but now they're going after NorBAC,
so we're running out of time.

38:45.646 --> 38:48.281
The truth is, David, I don't think
we can hold the research any longer.

38:48.468 --> 38:51.692
If we give this to Lowy, they're going
to figure out a way to make it their own.

38:51.927 --> 38:54.223
I'm sure they will.
It's a very powerful discovery.

38:54.345 --> 38:56.942
Yeah. A discovery
that was made by Harlan Sendak.

38:57.617 --> 39:00.051
Maybe you should talk to Laura?
See what she wants to do.

39:00.206 --> 39:02.383
Man, I already got
something in the works.

39:02.807 --> 39:05.381
- I could have come up.
- Nah-nah, it's all right.

39:05.725 --> 39:07.693
Did you want to talk
to me about something?

39:07.848 --> 39:09.612
- It can wait.
- Okay.

39:12.685 --> 39:14.283
You wanted to talk?

39:15.045 --> 39:16.712
Why did you let Owen back in?

39:16.937 --> 39:19.221
- What happened to "give the kid a chance"?
- I'm sorry.

39:19.337 --> 39:21.533
That was before
I knew he was using.

39:21.797 --> 39:24.050
Don't worry, he was clean
when he came home.

39:25.286 --> 39:26.881
He's lying to you, David.

39:27.535 --> 39:29.093
How'd you know that.

39:29.325 --> 39:30.821
I know addicts.

39:31.667 --> 39:32.860
All right.

39:36.728 --> 39:39.840
Okay. My "thing" was prescription pills.

39:40.267 --> 39:42.402
I went through treatment three times.

39:42.996 --> 39:45.283
And the third time worked.
It was eleven years ago, okay.

39:45.395 --> 39:48.212
- I've never gone back.
- Jill, I've seen you drink.

39:49.307 --> 39:51.530
Recovering addicts didn't drink.

39:52.456 --> 39:54.882
Right, well, alcohol
was never my addiction.

39:55.055 --> 39:56.990
Although I'm sure someday
it could be.

39:57.117 --> 39:58.820
Or cigarettes or God or...

39:59.997 --> 40:01.592
Who knows? Um...

40:02.306 --> 40:05.151
The only reason I'm telling
you this is because...

40:05.538 --> 40:07.572
I don't want you to
get hurt by Owen, okay?

40:07.687 --> 40:09.222
You can't trust him.

40:09.447 --> 40:11.382
He's not who you think he is.

40:14.565 --> 40:16.441
What do you want me to do, Jill?

40:18.095 --> 40:19.820
Just watch your back.

40:22.826 --> 40:24.202
Okay.

40:33.995 --> 40:35.711
- Hey.
- Hey.

40:36.328 --> 40:37.790
What's going on?

40:39.188 --> 40:40.473
Nothing.

40:40.725 --> 40:42.440
What'd you do today?

40:42.716 --> 40:44.260
Just chilled here.

40:45.578 --> 40:47.473
Got any plans for tomorrow?

40:47.856 --> 40:49.092
Not really.

40:56.647 --> 40:59.412
- You do any shit today?
- Meth?

41:00.685 --> 41:01.861
No.

41:02.856 --> 41:04.571
Do you want to?

41:06.607 --> 41:08.031
Yeah.

41:10.976 --> 41:13.501
Okay. Um...

41:15.548 --> 41:18.030
If you're going to stay here,
we gotta do something about that.

41:18.288 --> 41:19.921
I am.
I'm staying away from it.

41:20.067 --> 41:22.553
No. It's not just enough
to stay away from it, Owen.

41:22.635 --> 41:24.671
'Cause it's everywhere. It's like...

41:24.766 --> 41:27.092
It's like there's a bar
on every block in this town.

41:27.187 --> 41:29.760
Some days, I feel like
I could hit every one of them.

41:30.028 --> 41:31.483
You ever do that?

41:33.397 --> 41:35.560
Yeah, I've been known to.

41:35.648 --> 41:37.482
Okay, yeah, on occasion.

41:37.987 --> 41:40.192
But it's not a habit,
you understand what I'm saying?

41:40.666 --> 41:41.820
Yeah.

41:42.135 --> 41:44.280
Okay, so here's
what's going down.

41:44.368 --> 41:45.942
You're going to get some help

41:46.076 --> 41:47.863
and you're gonna enroll in

41:47.986 --> 41:50.292
a program that's going
to get you off the drugs.

41:50.487 --> 41:54.562
And then you're going to get a job. And
then you're going to get up every morning.

41:54.668 --> 41:56.392
And you're going to go to work.

41:56.577 --> 41:59.052
And you're going to live your life like,

41:59.168 --> 42:01.512
you know,
a relatively normal human being.

42:02.145 --> 42:03.952
- Okay.
- No. Just...

42:04.066 --> 42:06.840
I mean, yes, okay,
but don't just say "okay", okay?

42:06.928 --> 42:08.552
Because this is
what's going to happen, Owen.

42:08.597 --> 42:11.262
Or that door's going to hit you
on the ass on the way out, okay?

42:11.497 --> 42:13.952
David. I'm going to do this.

42:14.527 --> 42:16.323
I want to do this.

42:18.958 --> 42:20.051
Okay.

42:20.518 --> 42:21.823
Okay.

42:24.457 --> 42:25.892
Keep it down.

42:43.275 --> 42:44.461
Okay...

42:44.655 --> 42:46.302
You want me
to go in with you?

42:47.228 --> 42:48.892
Right. Got it.

42:49.385 --> 42:52.211
So, new city, new chance.

42:53.688 --> 42:55.572
I know it's cheesy,
but it's true.

42:56.726 --> 42:57.851
Thanks.

42:58.498 --> 43:00.233
See ya later.

43:46.155 --> 43:49.863
- Mayko?
- Right here, Jesus. God.

43:50.205 --> 43:53.311
Where's Harlan's hard drive?
His lab books. All his stuff?

43:53.825 --> 43:56.623
It was right here

43:56.835 --> 43:59.223
when I left yesterday.

43:59.395 --> 44:00.700
That's weird.

44:01.808 --> 44:03.121
Oh, no.

44:06.135 --> 44:08.171
Thank you for telling me all this.

44:08.257 --> 44:10.301
Harlan did some incredible work.

44:12.927 --> 44:14.533
It belongs to you now.

44:15.436 --> 44:18.220
- What is this?
- That is a patent.

44:18.517 --> 44:22.662
For the gene he discovered
and a compound that will turn it off.

44:23.545 --> 44:25.743
I was working all week
with a lawyer friend of mine.

44:25.835 --> 44:27.732
He wrangled it
through the patent office for you.

44:28.337 --> 44:32.302
So, now you can go to Lowy...
on your own terms if you want to.

44:33.956 --> 44:37.373
- Could be worth millions.
- Or it could hurt so many.

44:38.375 --> 44:39.411
Yeah.

44:39.978 --> 44:41.693
You'll have to think about it.

44:42.618 --> 44:44.031
Thank you.

44:45.898 --> 44:47.132
It's hard.

44:47.797 --> 44:49.840
We don't need millions of dollars.

44:50.435 --> 44:53.241
My children need their father
and I need Harlan.

44:54.515 --> 44:55.990
I know. I'm sorry.

44:57.316 --> 44:59.313
What would he have done?

45:01.398 --> 45:02.743
I don't know.

45:05.278 --> 45:07.010
I really don't know.

45:12.528 --> 45:14.493
- All right, where is it?
- Where's what?

45:14.628 --> 45:16.223
Harlan Sendak's research.

45:16.317 --> 45:18.523
We don't come up with it,
you're going to be arrested.

45:18.605 --> 45:22.002
Your apartment is going to be searched.
Laura Sendak's house is going to be searched--

45:22.337 --> 45:24.072
- It's in my car. I--
- Go!

45:28.195 --> 45:31.142
You pull something like that again,
I'm not going to cover your ass.

45:31.346 --> 45:33.331
- I'm tired of this, David.
- Come on.

45:33.566 --> 45:37.841
I thought it was my petulant, irresponsible
behavior that you loved about me.

45:37.938 --> 45:40.871
Okay. Moving on.
Any more suicides?

45:41.027 --> 45:44.812
Yeah, two more further up the Mississippi
in a place called Greanville, Arkansas.

45:44.895 --> 45:46.662
They haven't had a suicide since 1981.

45:46.798 --> 45:49.370
Well, I think it's
time for a little field research.

45:49.517 --> 45:51.393
So do I, so pack your bags.

45:53.695 --> 45:55.500
Oh. Where is it?

45:55.788 --> 45:58.410
I put it in here this afternoon,
Caroline. I fucking swear.

45:58.506 --> 46:00.540
- David.
- I fucking swear.

46:09.496 --> 46:10.973
Yes, I understand.

46:12.918 --> 46:15.033
I'll have it sent
over to you immediately.

46:15.696 --> 46:16.772
No.

46:17.188 --> 46:19.053
No one has any idea
what happened to it.

46:21.966 --> 46:23.313
Thank you, sir.

